cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formalizing requirements and enabling automated verification. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses an encoding from constrained PSPs to LTL formulas. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with reasoning about consistency and (in)consistency of requirements. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper mentions an artificial probabilistic model used to generate requirements of realistic size. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper discusses an embedded controller for a robotic manipulator.
